  "articleBody": "&lt;p&gt;The microwave gets a bad rap these days, but when you&rsquo;re running late or only have 10 minutes between errands, tossing a few ingredients in a mug for a healthy and tasty meal in five minutes flat doesn&rsquo;t sound too shabby. And all that hype about microwaves causing health concerns&mdash;well, it&rsquo;s just that. (There&rsquo;s not really &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/health/are-microwaves-really-health-hazard&quot;&gt;enough evidence&lt;/a&gt; to suggest they release enough radiation to be harmful.)&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;These breakfast, lunch, and dinner recipes are surprisingly flavorful and can be carried to work and cooked on the spot. If you&rsquo;re really anti-microwave, most of them can easily be made in the oven if you have a few extra minutes to spare. While the &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/dessert-recipes-for-one&quot;&gt;desserts&lt;/a&gt; might not be the most nutritious, they are the most delicious. And who would say no to chocolate cake that only takes five minutes? Not us.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;section class=&quot;slideshow list-image-full&quot; ng-controller=&quot;SlideshowListCtrl&quot; ng-init=&quot;init()&quot;&gt;
            &lt;h3&gt;Breakfast&lt;/h3&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://thebigmansworld.com/2015/09/11/healthy-1-minute-blueberry-muffin/&quot;&gt;1. Healthy 1-Minute Blueberry Muffin&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/bigmansworld.jpg?itok=kIXUMtm9&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Blueberry Muffin&quot;
              width=&quot;680&quot;
              height=&quot;1020&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;1. Healthy 1-Minute Blueberry Muffin&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The Big Man&amp;#039;s World                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Ok, so it might actually take two minutes. Inspired by the blueberry muffins at Starbucks, this version is healthier, faster to make, and tastier. Banana adds a little extra potassium and staying power to this breakfast of champions. And if you&rsquo;re in it for the long haul (12 minutes), you can make it in the oven.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://amyshealthybaking.com/blog/2015/10/02/single-serving-clean-chocolate-mug-cake/&quot;&gt;2. Single-Serving Clean Chocolate Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/amyshealthybaking.jpg?itok=FokYCtgX&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Chocolate Mug Cake&quot;
              width=&quot;1320&quot;
              height=&quot;1980&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;2. Single-Serving Clean Chocolate Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Amy&amp;#039;s Healthy Baking                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;It&rsquo;s like dessert for breakfast&mdash;but good for you (and it only takes five minutes to whip up). Whole-wheat flour, cocoa powder greek yogurt, and naturally sweetened with maple syrup, this mug cake is perfect for those days when you want a sweet start to the day. &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.theironyou.com/2015/09/paleo-cinnamon-roll-in-mug.html&quot;&gt;3. Paleo Cinnamon Roll in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/theironyou.jpg?itok=zcsE3liB&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Cinnamon Roll&quot;
              width=&quot;1200&quot;
              height=&quot;1472&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;3. Paleo Cinnamon Roll in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The Iron You                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;We&rsquo;re all about this pastry in a mug, especially when it&rsquo;s cooler outside and we want cinnamon in everything. This mug treat delivers all of the comforting flavors of a cinnamon-roll breakfast, but with more fiber and nutrition. And tbh, if you&rsquo;re running short on time, skip the frosting&mdash;you won&rsquo;t miss it (that much).&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.sugarandsoul.co/2015/01/peanut-butter-oatmeal-mug-cake.html&quot;&gt;4. Peanut Butter and Oatmeal Mug Cake for Two&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/sugarandsoul.jpg?itok=lEFyTtyk&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Peanut Butter Oatmeal Muffin&quot;
              width=&quot;900&quot;
              height=&quot;1350&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;4. Peanut Butter and Oatmeal Mug Cake for Two&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Sugar and Soul                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;The perfect excuse to eat cake for breakfast&mdash;after all, it&rsquo;s oatmeal and peanut butter, what cake could be healthier? Just mix it up, toss in the microwave, and you&rsquo;re out the door with a breakfast that won&rsquo;t leave you frantically rummaging through your desk for snacks one hour later.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.fromcalculustocupcakes.com/coconut-flour-pancake-in-a-mug/&quot;&gt;5. Coconut Flour Pancake in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/fromcalculustocupcakes.jpg?itok=UVOOjyKE&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Pancake&quot;
              width=&quot;740&quot;
              height=&quot;1150&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;5. Coconut Flour Pancake in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: From Calculus to Cupcakes                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Pancake &agrave; la souffle. It&rsquo;s fluffy, it&rsquo;s a pancake, and it&rsquo;s in a mug&mdash;it's everything you could want. Add some blueberries for a sweeter version or cheese if you&rsquo;re craving savory. Just don&rsquo;t forget to grease the mug with butter or else you&rsquo;ll have a very sad-looking mug at the end of your meal.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/5-microwave-breakfasts/&quot;&gt;6. Sweet Potato Hash in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbaking_1.jpg?itok=auz2Lcyq&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Sweet Potato Hash&quot;
              width=&quot;682&quot;
              height=&quot;1024&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;6. Sweet Potato Hash in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;This one takes a bit longer&mdash;11 minutes&mdash;but we're talking potatoes here. The sweet potatoes mixed with savory veggies and cheese are a perfect combination, not to mention sweet potato's great nutritional benefits, like its anti-cancer and anti-inflamatory properties.&lt;span contenteditable=&quot;false&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;&lt;cite data-cite-reference=&quot;&quot; class=&quot;citation-reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24921903&quot;&gt;Sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas [L.] Lam)--a valuable medicinal food: a review.&lt;/a&gt; Mohanraj R, Sivasankar S. Journal of medicinal food, 2014, Jun.;17(7):1557-7600.&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/span&gt; The touch of rosemary at the end adds the perfect finishing flavor.&lt;/p&gt;           &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.joyfulhealthyeats.com/2-minute-egg-omelet-mug/&quot;&gt;7. 2-Minute Egg Omelet in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/joyfulhealthyeats_0.jpg?itok=j5RkE_yD&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: 2 Minute Omelet &quot;
              width=&quot;715&quot;
              height=&quot;1073&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;7. 2-Minute Egg Omelet in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Joyful Healthy Eats                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Not to worry, egg lovers, we&rsquo;ve got you covered too. This blend of spinach, peppers, and tomato is awesome, but you can substitute any veggies or meat for a create-your-own style.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.bowlofdelicious.com/2015/05/12/5-minute-spinach-and-cheddar-microwave-quiche-in-a-mug/&quot;&gt;8. 5-Minute Spinach and Cheddar Microwave Quiche in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/bowlofdelicious.jpg?itok=dZgKcEPA&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Spinach and Cheddar Quiche&quot;
              width=&quot;1000&quot;
              height=&quot;1500&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;8. 5-Minute Spinach and Cheddar Microwave Quiche in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Bowl of Delicious                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;A warm and delicious way to get your veggies for the day, this recipe tastes rich and flavorful while staying healthy. There's no more I-don't-have-time-to-eat-breakfast excuses allowed. &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.thewannabechef.net/2011/10/24/hot-pumpkin-breakfast-quinoa/&quot;&gt;9. Hot Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa &lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thewannabechef.jpg?itok=CMfVmLEH&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa&quot;
              width=&quot;710&quot;
              height=&quot;768&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;9. Hot Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa &quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The Wannabe Chef                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;This recipe loads up on the good stuff&mdash;quinoa and pumpkin&mdash;and uses maple syrup to sweeten it up. Pop one of these bad boys in the microwave before work for a seasonal dish that doesn't go overboard.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;h3&gt;Lunch/Dinner&lt;/h3&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://healthynibblesandbits.com/egg-fried-rice-mug/&quot;&gt;10. Egg Fried Rice in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/healthynibblesandbits.jpg?itok=U3HzKphP&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Egg Fried Rice&quot;
              width=&quot;550&quot;
              height=&quot;827&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;10. Egg Fried Rice in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Healthy Nibbles and Bits                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Who knew you could make fried rice in a microwave? This recipe hits all the right (flavor) notes, and no one would ever guess it takes only a cup, a microwave, and a few (okay, maybe a bit more than that) ingredients. Just don&rsquo;t skimp on the cup size&mdash;we're talking a meal here.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/homemade-spaghettios-mug/&quot;&gt;11. Homemade Spaghetti-ohs in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbakingspaghettios.jpg?itok=nUhmCZM2&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Spaghetti-Os&quot;
              width=&quot;682&quot;
              height=&quot;1024&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;11. Homemade Spaghetti-ohs in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Yep, you read that right: Spaghetti-ohs (cue your ecstatic inner child)&mdash;only the adult version, which still only takes seven minutes to make and will have you reminiscing about the good old days. Fun tip: Freeze the leftover sauce in &lt;a href=&quot;http://greatist.com/eat/ice-cube-tray-uses&quot;&gt;ice cube trays&lt;/a&gt;, then just pull out and thaw when you&rsquo;re in a rush.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://theviewfromgreatisland.com/instant-microwave-macaroni-and-cheese-in-a-mug/&quot;&gt;12. Instant Mac &amp;amp; Cheese in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/aviewfromgreatisland.jpg?itok=mAZmKLXb&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Mac n Cheese&quot;
              width=&quot;654&quot;
              height=&quot;980&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;12. Instant Mac &amp; Cheese in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The View From Great Island                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Naturally, no mug recipe list would be complete without the tried-and-true mac n&rsquo; cheese. Only three ingredients&mdash;we don&rsquo;t count water&mdash;and you&rsquo;re on your way to comfort food heaven, minus the craft, pot, and mess.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/microwave-lasagna/&quot;&gt;13. Microwave Lasagna in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbakinglasagna.jpg?itok=Q5BCS04P&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Lasagna&quot;
              width=&quot;853&quot;
              height=&quot;1280&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;13. Microwave Lasagna in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;All you need is a minute&mdash;plus the thirty seconds it takes to throw the ingredients in a mug, but we&rsquo;re pretty sure you can deal with that. It&rsquo;s all the lasagna flavors you love sans noodles. Substitute in any meat, veggies, and sauce you want (you can even use pesto), and voila! It&rsquo;s like Little Italy came to you.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;h3&gt;Dessert&lt;/h3&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.thewheatlesskitchen.com/paleo-pumpkin-chocolate-chip-mug-cake/&quot;&gt;14. Paleo Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thewheatlesskitchen.jpg?itok=oQJwHTLP&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Cake&quot;
              width=&quot;681&quot;
              height=&quot;1066&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;14. Paleo Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The Wheatless Kitchen                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Another reason to indulge your fall pumpkin cravings. As far as desserts go, this one&rsquo;s pretty darn healthy&mdash;and gluten-free, although you could replace the coconut flour with regular if you&rsquo;re in the mood for the full whammy. Whatever you do, don&rsquo;t leave out the chocolate.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://kirbiecravings.com/2014/04/peanut-butter-mug-cake-eggless.html?utm_source=feedburner&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+KirbieCravings+(Kirbie+Cravings)&quot;&gt;15. Peanut Butter Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/kirbiecravingspbmug.jpg?itok=thMdQZgk&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Peanut Butter Mug Cake&quot;
              width=&quot;660&quot;
              height=&quot;780&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;15. Peanut Butter Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Kirbie Cravings                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;You&rsquo;ve gotta love PB for this one. It&rsquo;s a cupful of pure peanut-ty goodness and it only calls for (five!) ingredients you&rsquo;re bound to have on hand so you can whip it up at a moment&rsquo;s notice.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.kimscravings.com/2015/05/cinnamon-roll-microwave-mug-cake/&quot;&gt;16. Cinnamon Roll Microwave Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/kimscravings.jpg?itok=uX0VcuVa&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Cinnamon Roll Cake&quot;
              width=&quot;640&quot;
              height=&quot;960&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;16. Cinnamon Roll Microwave Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Kim&amp;#039;s Cravings                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Six minutes 'til heaven&mdash;warm, cinnamon-y, gooey heaven. And with maple syrup for sweetness, it&rsquo;s not all that bad for you either, especially if you opt for whole-wheat or spelt flour instead of white. We&rsquo;ll just take breakfast and make it dessert.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://ohmydearblog.com/2015/10/27/apple-crisp-in-a-mug/&quot;&gt;17. Apple Crisp in a Mug&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/ohmydearblog.jpg?itok=opwJkH-n&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Apple Crisp&quot;
              width=&quot;683&quot;
              height=&quot;1024&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;17. Apple Crisp in a Mug&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Oh My Dear Blog                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Apple pie made easy. You can go the traditional oven route, but if you&rsquo;re looking for a really quick treat, it takes only two and a half minutes in the microwave. Top it off with a little ice cream and ta-da! Gourmet gone simple.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://lacreativitedelafille.blogspot.com/2012/06/red-velvet-mug-cake.html&quot;&gt;18. Red Velvet Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/myhappyplace.jpg?itok=Foim3xN8&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Red Velvet&quot;
              width=&quot;736&quot;
              height=&quot;1103&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;18. Red Velvet Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: La Creativite de la Fille                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;We&rsquo;re not typically fans of adding dye to anything edible, but when it comes to red velvet cake, we can&rsquo;t help ourselves&mdash;especially if it&rsquo;s a cute single-serving cake! This is the ideal recipe to enjoy on a night in, and you won&rsquo;t have to worry about leftovers tempting you later.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://weelicious.com/2015/05/18/microwave-mug-double-chocolate-brownie-recipe/&quot;&gt;19. Microwave Mug Double Chocolate Brownie &lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Weelicious.jpg?itok=y--DIJx7&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Double Chocolate Brownie&quot;
              width=&quot;700&quot;
              height=&quot;1049&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;19. Microwave Mug Double Chocolate Brownie &quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Weelicious                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Our happy place usually involves chocolate&mdash;the more, the better. This recipe does chocolate right, and you don&rsquo;t even have to pull out a cake pan. Five minutes and you have a perfectly cooked brownie begging for a scoop of ice cream. Just be careful to not overcook, or it&rsquo;ll get tough and rubbery.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.fivehearthome.com/2016/04/14/lemon-poppy-seed-muffin-mug-cake/&quot;&gt;20. Lemon Poppy Seed Mug Cake&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/fivehearthomeusethis.jpg?itok=jS4U9I5L&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: Lemon Poppy Seed Cake&quot;
              width=&quot;700&quot;
              height=&quot;1049&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;20. Lemon Poppy Seed Mug Cake&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: Five Heart Home                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;For the citrus fans who don&rsquo;t go gaga over chocolate, this speckled beauty is for you.  It&rsquo;s the perfect blend of sour and sweet, ready in minutes. &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot;&gt;

        &lt;div class=&quot;title-wrapper&quot;&gt;
          &lt;h4&gt;
                          &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://thepaleomama.com/2013/09/pumpkin-pie-in-2-minutes/&quot;&gt;21. Pumpkin Pie in 2 Minutes&lt;/a&gt;
                      &lt;/h4&gt;
                  &lt;/div&gt;

                  &lt;div class=&quot;media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img
              src=&quot;http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thepaleomama.jpg?itok=8be9eLGn&quot;
              alt=&quot;Mug Meals: 2 Minute Pumpkin Pie&quot;
              width=&quot;682&quot;
              height=&quot;1024&quot;
                            pin-title=&quot;21. Pumpkin Pie in 2 Minutes&quot;                          /&gt;
                          &lt;div class=&quot;field-name-field-file-image-title-text&quot;&gt;
                                Photo: The Paleo Mama                              &lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;/div&gt;
        
        &lt;div class=&quot;slide-body&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;It doesn&rsquo;t get simpler than this&mdash;only a few ingredients, a mug, and a microwave. You can even leave out the crust if you&rsquo;re in the mood for pure pumpkin. You can use regular sugar or stevia, but we like maple syrup or honey best.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      
