      <div class="article-body block" data-scroll-reach-tracking="article-content-beginning">
                <div class="article-body-content" data-target-blank itemprop="articleBody">
  <p>The microwave gets a bad rap these days, but when youre running late or only have 10 minutes between errands, tossing a few ingredients in a mug for a healthy and tasty meal in five minutes flat doesnt sound too shabby. And all that hype about microwaves causing health concernswell, its just that. (Theres not really <a href="http://greatist.com/health/are-microwaves-really-health-hazard">enough evidence</a> to suggest they release enough radiation to be harmful.)</p>  <p>These breakfast, lunch, and dinner recipes are surprisingly flavorful and can be carried to work and cooked on the spot. If youre really anti-microwave, most of them can easily be made in the oven if you have a few extra minutes to spare. While the <a href="http://greatist.com/eat/dessert-recipes-for-one">desserts</a> might not be the most nutritious, they are the most delicious. And who would say no to chocolate cake that only takes five minutes? Not us.</p>  <section class="slideshow list-image-full" ng-controller="SlideshowListCtrl" ng-init="init()">
            <h3>Breakfast</h3>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://thebigmansworld.com/2015/09/11/healthy-1-minute-blueberry-muffin/">1. Healthy 1-Minute Blueberry Muffin</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/bigmansworld.jpg?itok=kIXUMtm9"
              alt="Mug Meals: Blueberry Muffin"
              width="680"
              height="1020"
                            pin-title="1. Healthy 1-Minute Blueberry Muffin"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The Big Man&#039;s World                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Ok, so it might actually take two minutes. Inspired by the blueberry muffins at Starbucks, this version is healthier, faster to make, and tastier. Banana adds a little extra potassium and staying power to this breakfast of champions. And if youre in it for the long haul (12 minutes), you can make it in the oven.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://amyshealthybaking.com/blog/2015/10/02/single-serving-clean-chocolate-mug-cake/">2. Single-Serving Clean Chocolate Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/amyshealthybaking.jpg?itok=FokYCtgX"
              alt="Mug Meals: Chocolate Mug Cake"
              width="1320"
              height="1980"
                            pin-title="2. Single-Serving Clean Chocolate Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Amy&#039;s Healthy Baking                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Its like dessert for breakfastbut good for you (and it only takes five minutes to whip up). Whole-wheat flour, cocoa powder greek yogurt, and naturally sweetened with maple syrup, this mug cake is perfect for those days when you want a sweet start to the day. </p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.theironyou.com/2015/09/paleo-cinnamon-roll-in-mug.html">3. Paleo Cinnamon Roll in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/theironyou.jpg?itok=zcsE3liB"
              alt="Mug Meals: Cinnamon Roll"
              width="1200"
              height="1472"
                            pin-title="3. Paleo Cinnamon Roll in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The Iron You                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Were all about this pastry in a mug, especially when its cooler outside and we want cinnamon in everything. This mug treat delivers all of the comforting flavors of a cinnamon-roll breakfast, but with more fiber and nutrition. And tbh, if youre running short on time, skip the frostingyou wont miss it (that much).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.sugarandsoul.co/2015/01/peanut-butter-oatmeal-mug-cake.html">4. Peanut Butter and Oatmeal Mug Cake for Two</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/sugarandsoul.jpg?itok=lEFyTtyk"
              alt="Mug Meals: Peanut Butter Oatmeal Muffin"
              width="900"
              height="1350"
                            pin-title="4. Peanut Butter and Oatmeal Mug Cake for Two"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Sugar and Soul                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>The perfect excuse to eat cake for breakfastafter all, its oatmeal and peanut butter, what cake could be healthier? Just mix it up, toss in the microwave, and youre out the door with a breakfast that wont leave you frantically rummaging through your desk for snacks one hour later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.fromcalculustocupcakes.com/coconut-flour-pancake-in-a-mug/">5. Coconut Flour Pancake in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/fromcalculustocupcakes.jpg?itok=UVOOjyKE"
              alt="Mug Meals: Pancake"
              width="740"
              height="1150"
                            pin-title="5. Coconut Flour Pancake in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: From Calculus to Cupcakes                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Pancake  la souffle. Its fluffy, its a pancake, and its in a mugit's everything you could want. Add some blueberries for a sweeter version or cheese if youre craving savory. Just dont forget to grease the mug with butter or else youll have a very sad-looking mug at the end of your meal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/5-microwave-breakfasts/">6. Sweet Potato Hash in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbaking_1.jpg?itok=auz2Lcyq"
              alt="Mug Meals: Sweet Potato Hash"
              width="682"
              height="1024"
                            pin-title="6. Sweet Potato Hash in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>This one takes a bit longer11 minutesbut we're talking potatoes here. The sweet potatoes mixed with savory veggies and cheese are a perfect combination, not to mention sweet potato's great nutritional benefits, like its anti-cancer and anti-inflamatory properties.<span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><cite data-cite-reference="" class="citation-reference"><a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24921903">Sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas [L.] Lam)--a valuable medicinal food: a review.</a> Mohanraj R, Sivasankar S. Journal of medicinal food, 2014, Jun.;17(7):1557-7600.</cite></span> The touch of rosemary at the end adds the perfect finishing flavor.</p>           </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.joyfulhealthyeats.com/2-minute-egg-omelet-mug/">7. 2-Minute Egg Omelet in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/joyfulhealthyeats_0.jpg?itok=j5RkE_yD"
              alt="Mug Meals: 2 Minute Omelet "
              width="715"
              height="1073"
                            pin-title="7. 2-Minute Egg Omelet in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Joyful Healthy Eats                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Not to worry, egg lovers, weve got you covered too. This blend of spinach, peppers, and tomato is awesome, but you can substitute any veggies or meat for a create-your-own style.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.bowlofdelicious.com/2015/05/12/5-minute-spinach-and-cheddar-microwave-quiche-in-a-mug/">8. 5-Minute Spinach and Cheddar Microwave Quiche in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/bowlofdelicious.jpg?itok=dZgKcEPA"
              alt="Mug Meals: Spinach and Cheddar Quiche"
              width="1000"
              height="1500"
                            pin-title="8. 5-Minute Spinach and Cheddar Microwave Quiche in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Bowl of Delicious                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>A warm and delicious way to get your veggies for the day, this recipe tastes rich and flavorful while staying healthy. There's no more I-don't-have-time-to-eat-breakfast excuses allowed. </p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.thewannabechef.net/2011/10/24/hot-pumpkin-breakfast-quinoa/">9. Hot Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa </a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thewannabechef.jpg?itok=CMfVmLEH"
              alt="Mug Meals: Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa"
              width="710"
              height="768"
                            pin-title="9. Hot Pumpkin Breakfast Quinoa "                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The Wannabe Chef                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>This recipe loads up on the good stuffquinoa and pumpkinand uses maple syrup to sweeten it up. Pop one of these bad boys in the microwave before work for a seasonal dish that doesn't go overboard.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <h3>Lunch/Dinner</h3>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://healthynibblesandbits.com/egg-fried-rice-mug/">10. Egg Fried Rice in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/healthynibblesandbits.jpg?itok=U3HzKphP"
              alt="Mug Meals: Egg Fried Rice"
              width="550"
              height="827"
                            pin-title="10. Egg Fried Rice in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Healthy Nibbles and Bits                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Who knew you could make fried rice in a microwave? This recipe hits all the right (flavor) notes, and no one would ever guess it takes only a cup, a microwave, and a few (okay, maybe a bit more than that) ingredients. Just dont skimp on the cup sizewe're talking a meal here.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/homemade-spaghettios-mug/">11. Homemade Spaghetti-ohs in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbakingspaghettios.jpg?itok=nUhmCZM2"
              alt="Mug Meals: Spaghetti-Os"
              width="682"
              height="1024"
                            pin-title="11. Homemade Spaghetti-ohs in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Yep, you read that right: Spaghetti-ohs (cue your ecstatic inner child)only the adult version, which still only takes seven minutes to make and will have you reminiscing about the good old days. Fun tip: Freeze the leftover sauce in <a href="http://greatist.com/eat/ice-cube-tray-uses">ice cube trays</a>, then just pull out and thaw when youre in a rush.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://theviewfromgreatisland.com/instant-microwave-macaroni-and-cheese-in-a-mug/">12. Instant Mac &amp; Cheese in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/aviewfromgreatisland.jpg?itok=mAZmKLXb"
              alt="Mug Meals: Mac n Cheese"
              width="654"
              height="980"
                            pin-title="12. Instant Mac & Cheese in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The View From Great Island                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Naturally, no mug recipe list would be complete without the tried-and-true mac n cheese. Only three ingredientswe dont count waterand youre on your way to comfort food heaven, minus the craft, pot, and mess.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.biggerbolderbaking.com/microwave-lasagna/">13. Microwave Lasagna in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/biggerbolderbakinglasagna.jpg?itok=Q5BCS04P"
              alt="Mug Meals: Lasagna"
              width="853"
              height="1280"
                            pin-title="13. Microwave Lasagna in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Bigger Bolder Baking                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>All you need is a minuteplus the thirty seconds it takes to throw the ingredients in a mug, but were pretty sure you can deal with that. Its all the lasagna flavors you love sans noodles. Substitute in any meat, veggies, and sauce you want (you can even use pesto), and voila! Its like Little Italy came to you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <h3>Dessert</h3>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.thewheatlesskitchen.com/paleo-pumpkin-chocolate-chip-mug-cake/">14. Paleo Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thewheatlesskitchen.jpg?itok=oQJwHTLP"
              alt="Mug Meals: Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Cake"
              width="681"
              height="1066"
                            pin-title="14. Paleo Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The Wheatless Kitchen                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Another reason to indulge your fall pumpkin cravings. As far as desserts go, this ones pretty darn healthyand gluten-free, although you could replace the coconut flour with regular if youre in the mood for the full whammy. Whatever you do, dont leave out the chocolate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://kirbiecravings.com/2014/04/peanut-butter-mug-cake-eggless.html?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+KirbieCravings+(Kirbie+Cravings)">15. Peanut Butter Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/kirbiecravingspbmug.jpg?itok=thMdQZgk"
              alt="Mug Meals: Peanut Butter Mug Cake"
              width="660"
              height="780"
                            pin-title="15. Peanut Butter Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Kirbie Cravings                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Youve gotta love PB for this one. Its a cupful of pure peanut-ty goodness and it only calls for (five!) ingredients youre bound to have on hand so you can whip it up at a moments notice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.kimscravings.com/2015/05/cinnamon-roll-microwave-mug-cake/">16. Cinnamon Roll Microwave Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/kimscravings.jpg?itok=uX0VcuVa"
              alt="Mug Meals: Cinnamon Roll Cake"
              width="640"
              height="960"
                            pin-title="16. Cinnamon Roll Microwave Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Kim&#039;s Cravings                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Six minutes 'til heavenwarm, cinnamon-y, gooey heaven. And with maple syrup for sweetness, its not all that bad for you either, especially if you opt for whole-wheat or spelt flour instead of white. Well just take breakfast and make it dessert.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://ohmydearblog.com/2015/10/27/apple-crisp-in-a-mug/">17. Apple Crisp in a Mug</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/ohmydearblog.jpg?itok=opwJkH-n"
              alt="Mug Meals: Apple Crisp"
              width="683"
              height="1024"
                            pin-title="17. Apple Crisp in a Mug"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Oh My Dear Blog                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Apple pie made easy. You can go the traditional oven route, but if youre looking for a really quick treat, it takes only two and a half minutes in the microwave. Top it off with a little ice cream and ta-da! Gourmet gone simple.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://lacreativitedelafille.blogspot.com/2012/06/red-velvet-mug-cake.html">18. Red Velvet Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/myhappyplace.jpg?itok=Foim3xN8"
              alt="Mug Meals: Red Velvet"
              width="736"
              height="1103"
                            pin-title="18. Red Velvet Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: La Creativite de la Fille                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Were not typically fans of adding dye to anything edible, but when it comes to red velvet cake, we cant help ourselvesespecially if its a cute single-serving cake! This is the ideal recipe to enjoy on a night in, and you wont have to worry about leftovers tempting you later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://weelicious.com/2015/05/18/microwave-mug-double-chocolate-brownie-recipe/">19. Microwave Mug Double Chocolate Brownie </a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/Weelicious.jpg?itok=y--DIJx7"
              alt="Mug Meals: Double Chocolate Brownie"
              width="700"
              height="1049"
                            pin-title="19. Microwave Mug Double Chocolate Brownie "                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Weelicious                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>Our happy place usually involves chocolatethe more, the better. This recipe does chocolate right, and you dont even have to pull out a cake pan. Five minutes and you have a perfectly cooked brownie begging for a scoop of ice cream. Just be careful to not overcook, or itll get tough and rubbery.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://www.fivehearthome.com/2016/04/14/lemon-poppy-seed-muffin-mug-cake/">20. Lemon Poppy Seed Mug Cake</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/fivehearthomeusethis.jpg?itok=jS4U9I5L"
              alt="Mug Meals: Lemon Poppy Seed Cake"
              width="700"
              height="1049"
                            pin-title="20. Lemon Poppy Seed Mug Cake"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: Five Heart Home                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>For the citrus fans who dont go gaga over chocolate, this speckled beauty is for you.  Its the perfect blend of sour and sweet, ready in minutes. </p>
        </div>
      </div>
                <div class="slide">

        <div class="title-wrapper">
          <h4>
                          <a target="_blank" href="http://thepaleomama.com/2013/09/pumpkin-pie-in-2-minutes/">21. Pumpkin Pie in 2 Minutes</a>
                      </h4>
                  </div>

                  <div class="media-g_full_width_inline_image media-element-container">
            <img
              src="http://greatist.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_main/public/thepaleomama.jpg?itok=8be9eLGn"
              alt="Mug Meals: 2 Minute Pumpkin Pie"
              width="682"
              height="1024"
                            pin-title="21. Pumpkin Pie in 2 Minutes"                          />
                          <div class="field-name-field-file-image-title-text">
                                Photo: The Paleo Mama                              </div>
                      </div>
        
        <div class="slide-body">
          <p>It doesnt get simpler than thisonly a few ingredients, a mug, and a microwave. You can even leave out the crust if youre in the mood for pure pumpkin. You can use regular sugar or stevia, but we like maple syrup or honey best.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
  </section>
  <p><br /><em>Originally posted December 2015. Updated July 2016.</em></p>         </div>

